		<p>Great!  I&#8217;d love it if you&#8217;d join the Azimuth Project.  I see you&#8217;ve become a member of the <a href="http://www.math.ntnu.no/~stacey/Mathforge/Azimuth" rel="nofollow">Forum</a> &mdash; good start! </p>
<p>Right now the top-priority projects seem to be:</p>
<p>&bull; Working through some well-known <a href="http://www.azimuthproject.org/azimuth/show/Plans+of+action" rel="nofollow">plans of action</a> &mdash; strategies for dealing with global warming &mdash; and summarizing them, discussing them here on the blog, critiquing them, and eventually maybe trying to formulate our own.</p>
<p>&bull; Making it easier for scientists, engineering and computer people to understand <a href="http://www.azimuthproject.org/azimuth/show/Climate+model" rel="nofollow">climate models</a>.  </p>
<p>There are also a lot of other projects to do, and I think it&#8217;s good for everyone to work on things that are fun and take advantage of their special skills.</p>
<p>We can talk more about this on the Forum if you like.</p>

