		<p>Dear John Baez,<br />
I continue to find your posts inspiring, and I would like to share with you the completion of the first stage of my harmonograph-as-a-work-of-art project, documented on my new site anitachowdry.com. Here is a page of drawings that the beast has produced : <a href="http://www.anitachowdry.com/iron-genie-drawings/4582085804" rel="nofollow ugc">http://www.anitachowdry.com/iron-genie-drawings/4582085804</a>  I couldn&#8217;t begin to describe the maths in them, but they do inspire me with an almost Pythagorean sense of awe.<br />
The machine is now ready to be loaned/hired out for for public appearances, so if anyone has any ideas about institutions that would like to have it for a period of public engagement, I would be most interested to hear from them.<br />
I hope you enjoy the Iron Genie beast,  Anita</p>

