		<p>Hello John</p>
<p>Yes you are right, and I am not saying this anymore.</p>
<p>However, if you make the assumption that the scalar part is nonzero, then there do exist such objects. I call them novanions, and they are in chapter 5 of the eBook in preparation called Superexponential Algebra. There is more than one type, and the theory is not now in conflict with any well-established mathematical result.</p>
<p>Jim H Adams</p>

